- Use Settings button to switch between cockpit and cabin modes or change preferences. You can chose wich patterns to display in the main screens via the [Show list] button.<br/><br/><b>Cockpit mode</b><br/>- Enter start time of the first rest and end time of the last rest by tapping the proper fields<br/><br/>- Set the time (pause) between two rests.<br/><br/>- If using Cockpit mode based on takeoff and landing, you can also enter flight time. Landing time will then be computed provided takeoff time has been entered and vice versa. Set the times between takeoff and first rest, between last rest and landing via the two horizontal cursors.<br/><br/>- Choose one of the patterns. 2R (or 3R) means a period 2 (or 3) times longer than the reference rest. "x" means a user defined rest period.<br/><br/>- Round and/or modify rest times if necessary. Touch a rest turns it magenta which means it is selected, and can now be modify with plus and minus buttons.<br/><br/><b>Cabin mode</b><br/>- Choose between the proposed patterns. If your airline use a different one, mail me with the details and I\'ll try to include it ;-)<br/><br/>- Enter start time of the first rest and end time of the last rest or service by tapping the proper fields<br/><br/>- Set the time (pause) between two rests (or between rest and service). If you want a pause after a service followed by a rest, check the appropriate box in the settings screen.<br/><br/>- Set service(s) duration(s). If you use keypad page, you will be able to memorize preset durations in Mem buttons. Just type a duration with the keypad and long press the Mem button where you want the preset to be. Clear the field and long press the preset you want to erase.<br/><br/><i>ZzTrop is free software, but if you feel like donating, please help yourself by going to my website (the "www" button).<br/><br/>The developer, Cyril Real</i><br/><br/>cyril.real@gmail.com<br/>http://cyril.real.free.fr